-- Ex-Chairman of Taiwan Auto Lights Maker to Plead Guilty in U.S.
-- B y   J o e l   R o s e n b l a t t
-- 2012-02-25T05:01:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-24/ex-chairman-of-taiwan-auto-lights-maker-will-plead-guilty-1-.html
The former chairman of  Depo Auto
Parts Industrial Co. (6605)  agreed to plead guilty to participating in
a price-fixing conspiracy, the U.S. Justice Department said in
an e-mailed statement.  According to a felony charge filed yesterday in U.S.
District Court in San Francisco, Shiu-Min Hsu conspired to
eliminate competition by fixing the prices of aftermarket auto
lights. according to the statement. Depo Auto Parts, based in
Taiwan, sells the lights that are used in repairs following a
collision or as accessories and upgrades.  “The international price-fixing conspiracy in the
aftermarket auto lights industry caused harm to businesses and
consumers,” Sharis A. Pozen, acting assistant attorney general
in charge of the Justice Department’s Antitrust Division, said
in the statement.  The case is U.S. v. Hsu, 12-cr-0121, U.S. District Court,
Northern District of  California  ( San Francisco ).  To contact the reporter on this story:
